{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reinstate driving instructors/trainers removed from the register during Covid-19",
        "additional_details": "All decisions made by the Government should take into account the effects of Covid-19. The Government must urgently ensure driving instructors are not disadvantaged by the impact of Covid-19. \r\nThose who hire vehicles, buy on-hire purchase and/or are paying for a franchise must not to be treated harshly & unfairly. Those removed from the Register will be hit harder as they will have no job to return to.",
        "background": "The Government should reinstate Approved Driving Instructors who cancel a Standards Check & PDIs who cancel a Part 3 Test due to concerns about Covid-19, variants, health issues & vulnerable family. DVSA should return all badges & reinstate those removed from Register (inc. driver/rider trainers).",
